author: DAN ALBANO
title: Roundup: Troy opens Freeway showcase by sinking Sunny Hills
text:
Roundup: Troy opens Freeway showcase by sinking Sunny Hills September 30, 2015 11:21 PM BY DAN ALBANO OCVARSITY.COM 
Andrew Kim scored five goals -- all from from center -- and Nathan Pak added three as Troy's boys water polo team defeated Sunny Hills, 12-8, in the teams' Freeway League opener at Fullerton on Wednesday night. 
Nick Van Steenhuyse added a goal, three assists and seven steals for the Warriors. 
The Freeway League has moved to a single-round format and is hosting league showcases Wednesday nights at different schools. The Division 4 league will host a playoff finale to determine playoff seeding. 
Also in the Freeway: 
Sonora 16, La Habra 8: County-leading scorer Conrad Napier scored five goals and Ben Angulo added four to pace the Raiders in their league opener at Fullerton. 
In the Orange League: 
Katella 4, Santa Ana Valley 3: 
Julio Sandino made 15 saves and Anthony Marin scored the lone goal of the fourth period to lift the visiting Knights in their league opener. 
In nonleague: 
Los Alamitos 15, San Clemente 11: Center Adam Lott scored eight goals to lead the visiting Griffins.
